des:
Westinghouse Smart Plug products help you control home appliance.You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your plug.
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your plug - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
After connecting Alexa to your Westinghouse Smart Plug products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "Westinghouse Smart Plug" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register an account in our "Westinghouse Smart Plug" app;
(3). You need to have some Westinghouse Smart Plug devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "Westinghouse Smart Plug" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Westsmart" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Westsmart" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Westsmart", and you'll be navigated to "Westsmart" login page;
(9). Open "Westinghouse Smart Plug" App, click More Service, choose "Alexa". Link with Verification Code, copy the Code, put code into the login page；
(10). Now all setup is finished.
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on plug.”
“Alexa, turn off plug.”
